Joseph C. ROSS v. UNITED STATES of America. No. 8004. Circuit Court of Appeals, Sixth Circuit. Oct. 10, 1938. Zeno Fritz, of Pittsburgh, Pa., for appellant. Francis C. Canny, of Cincinnati, Ohio, for appellee.

Before HICKS, SIMONS, and ALLEN, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

It is ordered that the appeal in this cause be and the same is dismissed, pursuant to stipulation of counsel.
